- The custom scoring formula is calculated as: (touchdowns * 6) + ((passes completed - interceptions) * 0.5) + (rushing yards / 10);
- The game types include regular season, playoffs, and championship;
- The results can be either Win or Loss.

sql:
SELECT AVG(yards_gained) AS avg_yards_gained
FROM player_stats
WHERE rushing_attempts > 10;

external_knowledge:
- "Injured the most" refers to players with the highest number of injuries;
- "Most recent injury" refers to the latest injury a player has suffered;
- "Context of the game" includes the year, week, and day of the week the game took place.

- A 'Good season' is defined as having more than 10 games, an average rushing yards allowed less than 100, an average passing yards allowed less than 200, and an average yards allowed per play less than 5;
- A 'Fair season' is defined as having more than 5 games, an average rushing yards allowed less than 120, an average passing yards allowed less than 250, and an average yards allowed per play less than 6;
- Any season not meeting the criteria for 'Good' or 'Fair' is classified as 'Poor'.

- "unscathed or recently recovered athletes" refers to players who have not been injured or have been injured after August 31, 2022;
- "typically traverse per match" refers to the average yards gained per game;
- "graced the field more than five times" means they have played in more than 5 games;
- "most prolific runners leading the pack" indicates that the results are ordered by the average yards gained per game in descending order.

- A "linebacker" is a defensive position in football, typically responsible for tackling and covering receivers;
- "Regular season" refers to the main part of a sports league's competition, excluding playoffs or championships;
- "Years active" refers to the duration a player has been playing professionally.

- "AFC" stands for the American Football Conference, one of the two conferences in the NFL (National Football League);
- "Total yards gained" refers to the cumulative distance a player advances the ball during a game;
- "Rank = 1" indicates the player with the highest total yards gained within their team.

sql:
SELECT AVG(ps.receiving_yards) AS AverageReceivingYardsPerGame
FROM injuries i
JOIN player_stats ps ON i.player_id = ps.player_id AND i.game_id = ps.game_id;
